cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about learning a shared dialog structure from a set of task-oriented dialogs, which is a topic related to natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a modified VRNN model with discrete latent vectors, which involves machine learning techniques and could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the learned dialog structure in a downstream task, which could be related to cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
